// (5) bank code + account range to new bank code + same account
//
// Each group of mappings is preceded by a format line in square brackets that determines how the group is structured.
// Each format specifier contains as first value the IBAN rule it applies to.
// There must be at least 2 values and at most 4 values. The possible format is made so flexible that it is easy
// to update values from the specification by simply copy and pasting (mostly). Each entry in the format specifier corresponds to an entry
// in the data line. Values beyond entries in the format specifier are ignored.
//
// The following fields are allowed:
// #sc - source bank code
// #sa - source account
// #ss - source account range, start value
// #se - source account range, end value
// #tc - target bank code
// #ta - target account
// _   - ignore entry
//
// If any of the target entries is missing then its source value is used for it (i.e. no mapping).
// Each entry can have a fixed value by adding it directly to the marker. This allows e.g. to specify a bank code
// for a group of mappings instead of having it to be written explicitely for every mapping line.
